{
  "stem": "27767.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "10 kilometers, about 10, 12 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the third or the fourth day after he went back, he sent me a note with this man-- which I didn't know at that time-- with this man with a wagon, who went with the dads-- who took the dads to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know he found him there how.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He sent me a note, he's fine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They checked him out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the doctor there told me he had pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he sent notes back to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He has no pneumonia, but he has a very bad cold, and he's much better.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we couldn't get him-- bring him back there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was there and this man, I was able to send with him-- after, you know, I was working in the warehouse and going for bread.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was really able to send him a bread, every week a bread or some bread and some margarine and some jell-o And write him a letter, which was unheard of there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And able to get back answer from him, he got it, and he's OK.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we kept on this-- because this was sometime in February '45.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We kept in on through April, about two, three, weeks-- two weeks before the liberation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then it stopped, everything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't send this guy anymore to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I didn't hear from him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was sure he was alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was sure he was going to be liberated there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and then I find out what's happened after the liberation, which we'll go back to that when we talk about--",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Allach I was actually since August through the liberation, which was April 27, I think, '45.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So about nine months, 10 months I was in Allach, all the time.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
